main event: Two luminous objects were observed at dusk maintaining the same relative position in the sky.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 20 minutes, with the observer noting that one object was smaller and fainter than the other., The objects appeared to be rotating on top and flat on the bottom., The initial sighting was at an elevation of 25 degrees., No sound was heard during the observation., A retired Lieutenant Colonel reported the objects were likely celestial bodies, attributing their brilliance to a clear atmosphere after a cold front.
sighted object: two luminous objects in the sky
witness description: A 39-year-old salesman from a TV shop, with unknown reliability.
